description:
In a world with thousands of religions, choosing the right path is a challenge. How do we know which one to follow? When exploring faith, we are faced with two options: we can choose the wide, easy path or the narrow, difficult journey. Who chooses the narrow road and why? How do we heed God’s warnings, transform our lives, and stay committed?
Trusting God in trials can be challenging, but it's vital to follow His lead and focus on obedience. Our faith is strengthened by trials, and we're not alone; God remains faithful to His people. Join MacKenzie Drebit in 'Odd, Singular, Strait-laced Extremists' for insights and answers to these questions and more!
